'''Gédéon Tshingoma Kalulu Kyatengwa''' (born 29 August 1997) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]] for Cypriot club [[Aris Limassol FC|Aris Limassol]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]].

== Early life ==
Kalulu was born in the [[8th arrondissement of Lyon]], France, and is Congolese by descent.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Bonnaud |first=Mickael |date=2 February 2017 |title=Gédéon Kalulu : " Je m'inspire de ce que fait Samuel Umtiti " |url=https://www.olympique-et-lyonnais.com/gedeon-kalulu-je-minspire-de-ce-que-fait-samuel-umtiti,129919.html |website=Olympique & Lyonnais}}</ref> His father was born in Kabimba, [[Belgian Congo]], and his mother in [[Likasi]], [[Congo-Léopoldville]]. He acquired [[French nationality law|French nationality]] on 26 December 2000 through the collective effect of his parents' [[naturalization]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Journal officiel de la République française n° 0303 du 31 décembre 2000 - Légifrance |url=https://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/jorf/jo/id/JORFCONT000000006763 |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=legifrance.gouv.fr |language=fr |format=PDF}}</ref>

==Club career==
A youth product of [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]], Kalulu signed his first professional contract with the club on 19 April 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ol.fr/Contents/Articles/2017/04/19/gedeon-kalulu-signe-un-premier-contrat-pro-de-3-ans-avec-lol-30701|title=Gédéon Kalulu signe un premier contrat pro de 3 ans avec l'OL|website=www.OL.fr}}</ref> After a season on loan with [[Football Bourg-en-Bresse Péronnas 01|Bourg-en-Bresse]], Kalulu signed with [[AC Ajaccio|Ajaccio]] on 24 July 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://maligue2.fr/2019/07/24/mercato-gedeon-kalulu-vers-lac-ajaccio/|title=Mercato - Gédéon Kalulu vers l'AC Ajaccio|date=24 July 2019|website=MaLigue2}}</ref> He made his debut for Ajaccio in a 4–1 [[Coupe de la Ligue]] win over [[Valenciennes FC|Valenciennes]] on 13 August 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ca.soccerway.com/matches/2019/08/13/france/coupe-de-la-ligue/athletic-club-ajaccien/valenciennes-anzin-football-club/3082721/|title=Ajaccio vs. Valenciennes - 13 August 2019 - Soccerway|website=ca.soccerway.com}}</ref>

On 3 June 2022, Kalulu signed a four-year contract with [[FC Lorient|Lorient]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Lorient|url=https://fclweb.fr/gedeon-kalulu-un-leopard-chez-les-merlus/|title=GÉDÉON KALULU, UN LÉOPARD CHEZ LES MERLUS|date=3 June 2022|access-date=7 July 2022|language=fr}}</ref>

On 18 August 2025, Kalulu joined [[Aris Limassol FC|Aris Limassol]] in Cyprus on a three-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Aris Limassol FC|url=https://arisfc.com/en/news/gedeon-kalulu-is-green-2025-08-18/|title=Gédéon Kalulu is Green|date=18 August 2025|access-date=18 August 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
On 22 September 2020, Kalulu was called-up by the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sport365.fr/rd-congo-six-nouveaux-chez-les-leopards-mais-pas-disasi-9963785.html|title=RD Congo : Six nouveaux chez les Léopards, mais pas Disasi|trans-title=DR Congo: Six new among the Leopards, but not Disasi|language=fr|date=22 September 2020|accessdate=22 September 2020}}</ref> On 13 October 2020, he debuted for DR Congo in a 1–1 friendly tie with [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/10/13/world/friendlies/morocco/congo-dr/3369318/|title=Morocco vs. Congo DR - 13 October 2020 - Soccerway|website=Soccerway}}</ref>

On 27 December 2023, he was selected from the list of 24 Congolese players selected by [[Sébastien Desabre]] to compete in the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].

==Personal life==
He is the brother of fellow professional footballers [[Nantong Zhiyun F.C.|Nantong Zhiyun]] forward [[Aldo Kalulu|Aldo]] and [[FC Juventus]] defender [[Pierre Kalulu]], as well as [[Pau FC]] left-back [[Joseph Kalulu]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/club/lyon/167/blog/post/3108405/introducing-aldo-kalulu-rwandas-first-footballing-superstar|title=Aldo Kalulu: Rwanda's first football superstar?|date=10 September 2016|website=ESPN.com}}</ref>

